      "properties": {
        "text": ""
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "\u2139\ufe0f JHPixelProUnwrapFace (S-11) \u2014 chain demo: Load \u2192 S-06 \u2192 [mock AI edit] \u2192 S-11 \u2192 composite\n\nDefaults: feather_radius=16.0, mask_override=None.\n\nCHAIN PIPELINE (this workflow):\n  LoadImage \u2192 S-06 FacialAligner \u2192 ImageInvert (stand-in for an AI face-edit block) \u2192 S-11 UnwrapFace \u2192 PreviewImage A/B (before vs composited).\n\nReplace ImageInvert with your real AI edit chain (ControlNet, IPAdapter, inpaint, face-detail) wired on the aligned crop. The inverse_matrix_json wire from S-06 is required so S-11 knows where to warp the edit back onto the original canvas.\n\nWIDGETS:\n- inverse_matrix_json (converted to input pin): wire from S-06.inverse_matrix_json. Default identity 1x3x3 is a safe pass-through if you disconnect the wire.\n- feather_radius (pixels): Gaussian blur on the auto-generated mask. 16 is a good portrait default. Higher = smoother blend; 0 = hard edge. Ignored when mask_override is wired.\n- mask_override (optional MASK): wire a custom skin-only / SAM mask upstream to restrict composite to that region.\n\nROUND-TRIP IDENTITY (sanity test):\n  If you replace ImageInvert with a passthrough (or set ImageInvert.mode bypass), the composite should approximate the original. Two bilinear resamples (align + unwarp) plus the feather will soften details slightly \u2014 expected ~10\u201334/255 in uint8. Good enough for retouch chains, not near-lossless.\n\nMASK OUTPUT:\nThe mask_used MASK output exposes the feathered face region in canvas coords. Wire it downstream into ImageBlend for advanced compositing modes (multiply, screen) instead of the built-in alpha-over."
      ],
      "color": "#243",
      "bgcolor": "#365"
    }
